==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-honest.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more-most}}

#(of a person or institution) [[Scrupulous]] with regard to telling the [[truth]]; not given to [[swindling]], [[lying]], or [[fraud]]
#:''Has the president been honest with us?''
#(of a statement) true, esp. true as far as the knowledge of the person making the statement.
#in good [[faith]]; without malice (''an honest mistake'')
#fair; unbiased (''an honest account of events'')
#(of measurement devices) accurate (''an honest scale'')
#veritable; full (''an honest day's work'')

